column35: active flyers (Padian 1983) and mostly piscivorous (Wang and Zhou 2006)
lacks "any adaptation for efficient swimming" and "did not swim but lived along the shoreline... patrolling.. in search for food" in the water
viviparous based on O'Keefe and Chiappe 2011

successive stem group taxa Sinoconodon, Morganucodon, Megazostrodon, and Hadroconium were all insectivorous (Jenkins and Parrington 1976; Luo et al. 2001) and Megazostrodon and Eozostrodon were scansorial (Jenkins and Parrington 1976)

See Jenkins, Jr. and Parrington (1976)\r\nWhatley and Carrano set this to scansorial insectivore oviparous and I am unsetting it because it causes all sorts of bizarre problems; individual orders and families should be set instead
see also Simpson 1937 Bull USNM, who hypothesizes that multis were largely arboreal
